This class encapsulates the results of the normalisation process for a Xena Input source.

When a XenaInputSource is to be normalised, a number of things may happen to it:

  • It is normalised properly.
  • There is a problem during normalisation.
  • It is found to be a 'child' of another XenaInputSource

When a XenaInputSource is normalised correctly, in the normalised flag will be set to true. In this case, the following information is set in the results object:

  • normaliser information
  • the version of Xena
  • the type of the XenaInputSource
  • FileNamer
  • MetaDataWrapper
  • Xena ID

If an error occurs during normalising, then the normalised flag should be set to false. In this case, if an exception has been thrown or an error condition has arisen, these should be appended to the errorList or exceptionList as appropriate. If this normaliser results object corresponds to a XenaInputSource that will be embedded in the output of another XenaInputSource when it is normalised, then this will be reflected in the results object, by setting the isChild flag to true, and setting the parentSystemId.
